    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="279" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d279">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No official record of this conversation has been found. The only reference to the
                    meeting occurs in the notes by <persName corresp="#p_DJPJ1">John P.
                        Davies</persName> on what <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName>
                    told <persName corresp="#p_SJW1">Stilwell</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJPJ1">Davies</persName> on December 6. According to the
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJPJ1">Davies</persName> notes, <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> said that he had had a three-hour
                    conversation with the Chiangs on the evening before his departure for Tehran.
                    With respect to subjects discussed, <persName corresp="#p_HHL1"
                        >Hopkins</persName> mentioned only that the Chiangs had raised the question
                    of the return of Outer Mongolia. This question had been brought up at the dinner
                    meeting on November 23, 1943; see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                        target="#pg_325">p. 325</ref>.</p>
                <p>The <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> notes reproduced on the facing
                    page may pertain to this conversation.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
